choices.text:
dealing with people coming from time to time and complaining that the sun doesn't shine anymore. Like, I get it, 6 weeks of rain isn't the best thing to deal with everyday, but you still have 46 weeks, that's so much time during which the sun DOES shine. It sounds ridiculous, but if it rains for a whole week, I hear the "Can't the sun please stop raining?". I guess I can't blame them, I do it everywhere else too, even in Spain. But it's a bit crazy... and I'm the first to agree with all this rain and clouds. Sometimes I even complain, but specially because after a week of rain, it starts snowing, that's what I don't get.

It rains. It snows. It's all the same.... it's just not the changing of the seasons that I'm used to. I've spent nearly my whole life in a warmer climate. I do hope that April is spring, not winter, and I can pretend that the snow isn't there.

What's it like in other places of the US, or internationally? How does your calendar work?
